The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Jan. 19: Niko Resources of Canada has found oil in offshore Hazira, Gujarat. The third well, Hazira OS-3, drilled from the offshore platform tested oil at 1,200 metres with a flowing rate of 6,000 barrels per day, a company official said. ?The oil zone has now been successfully tested in five wells and can be identified on logs in nine wells in the Hazira field,? he added. OS-3 will now be completed as a gas well and immediately put on production.

 New Delhi, Jan 19: Adobe will hire 150 people in India in 2005, taking the headcount to 525. It today inaugurated the second phase of its campus facility in Noida.

 New Delhi, Jan. 19: The Insurance Regulatory and Development Authority will come up with a comprehensive scheme for the poor within two weeks to cover all types of risks at a nominal cost.

 New Delhi, Jan. 19: Thirty-eight power projects, having a combined generation capacity of 12,183 MW, are likely to slip to the next plan period despite the ministry?s efforts to meet the Tenth Plan capacity addition target.

 Bangalore, Jan. 19: Intel expects the sales of laptops in India to exceed to over 3 lakh units in 2005 with its Centrino mobile chip being the market driver.




